      • isPreviousRequestRelevent

        public static boolean isPreviousRequestRelevent​(MonacoRange prev,
                                                MonacoRange next)
        Determines whether or not a historical request affects the current request.
        Parameters:
        prev - previous, historical request
        next - current request
        Returns:
        true when prev range is at same spot or before next range - i.e prev will affect next's range when transformed, false otherwise

      • isRangeOverlap

        public static boolean isRangeOverlap​(MonacoRange prev,
                                     MonacoRange next)
        Determines whether or not there is range overlap in any direction between prev and next
        Parameters:
        prev - previous, historical request
        next - current request
        Returns:
        true when there is any overlap in the MonacoRanges of prev and next. False otherwise.

      • resolveConflictingRanges

        public static StringChangeRequest[] resolveConflictingRanges​(StringChangeRequest prev,
                                                             StringChangeRequest next)
        Shifts the range of next to remove selection that both prev and next delete/replace
        Parameters:
        prev - previous, historical request
        next - current request that can be altered
        Returns:
        List of at most 2 requests. The first element is the original request that may have be altered. the second element is either null or a second request generated from splitting two ranges
